## 8. Server-Owned Codex Prompt Delivery

- [x] Confirm session action/intent calls are the only client path for workflow prompts.

- [x] Confirm the client never writes prompt text to the Codex terminal websocket.

- [x] Server session service receives action/intent input.

- [x] Server runtime updates the step machine.

- [x] Server terminal service starts or reuses the visible Codex terminal.

- [x] Server terminal service injects the prompt into that terminal.

- [x] Server terminal service records prompt handoff metadata.

- [x] Server service emits session changed after the status moves into an awaiting/executing phase.

- [x] Server service emits terminal changed/output events through the existing terminal/session event path.

- [x] Client attaches to `presentation.terminal.codex.terminalSessionId` for display only.

- [x] Autopilot terminal attachment is read-only.

- [x] Inspect terminal attachment remains interactive.

- [x] Add focused server tests:
  - Prompt action creates or reuses visible Codex terminal.
  - Prompt action injects exactly once.
  - Repeated submission while awaiting agent result is rejected by server.
  - Prompt delivery failure is visible and does not pretend state succeeded.

- [x] Add focused Playwright tests:
  - Autopilot prompt submit posts only to session action/intent route.
  - Browser never sends prompt text to terminal websocket.
  - Transparent terminal preview appears only when server presentation says terminal is visible.
  - Transparent terminal preview disappears when server presentation changes to input.

## 9. Server-Owned Command Execution Semantics

- [x] Decide whether command actions remain browser-dispatched terminal starts or become fully server-dispatched.

- [x] If command execution remains browser-dispatched:
  - Server `nextOperation` must explicitly say `route: "command-terminal"`.
  - Client only executes that route with server-provided payload.
  - Client does not inspect action type.

- [x] If command execution becomes server-dispatched:
  - Session action/intent endpoint starts command terminal server-side.
  - Client only watches command output presentation.
  - Server emits events for command terminal lifecycle and session state changes.

- [x] Pick the simpler architecture and remove the other path.

- [x] Command success/failure effects must be written by server services.

- [x] Command failure must become server presentation, not client-invented workflow state.

- [x] Add focused server tests:
  - Command start records `actionStarted`.
  - Command close records result/effects and `actionFinished`.
  - Failed command produces server presentation requiring attention.

- [x] Add focused Playwright tests:
  - Autopilot dispatches command only when `nextOperation` explicitly routes to command.
  - Fake `action.type: "command"` alone does nothing.
  - Command failure screen comes from server presentation.

## 10. Server-Owned Inputs, Forms, Questions, And File Confirmation

- [x] Keep questions as pure UI sugar.
  - Questions may be rendered nicely.
  - Questions must not create separate durable workflow statuses.
  - Questions must map to `waiting_for_input` plus server-provided input presentation.

- [x] Keep `confirm_files` as a distinct structured review phase.

- [x] Server presentation for input must include:
  - title
  - prompt/message
  - fields
  - submit label
  - target intent/action/request
  - stale-state token if required

- [x] Server presentation for file confirmation must include:
  - files
  - editable content or references
  - accept intent
  - reject intent
  - feedback field
  - validation rules

- [x] Client renders input fields generically.

- [x] Client renders file confirmation generically.

- [x] Client submits the server-provided intent/request.

- [x] Client does not decide what rejection means.

- [x] State machine decides:
  - accept -> done/advance-ready/next state
  - reject -> awaiting_agent_result
  - reject plus Codex clarification -> awaiting_agent_result -> waiting_for_input

- [x] Add focused server tests for file confirmation transitions.

- [x] Add focused Playwright tests:
  - Waiting-for-input question renders as form and submits generic request.
  - Confirm-files renders file review, not conversation form.
  - Reject files sends feedback and server presentation transitions to awaiting agent.
  - Later server transition to waiting-for-input renders question form.

## 11. Realtime Events Owned By Services

- [x] Identify every service method that changes session state.

- [x] Ensure that service emits session-changed event after successful state change.

- [x] Ensure terminal service emits terminal/session events after terminal lifecycle changes.

- [x] Do not emit events from random route handlers unless the route handler is the service boundary.

- [x] Events must carry enough information for the client to refetch or patch the right session.

- [x] Event ordering must be simple:
  - write durable state,
  - build/enrich presentation,
  - emit event,
  - return response.

- [x] Add focused server tests:
  - `advanceSession` emits.
  - `rewindSession` emits.
  - `runSessionAction` emits before and after Codex prompt delivery when state changes.
  - `runSessionIntent` emits.
  - command terminal close emits.
  - prompt delivery failure emits visible failure.

- [x] Add focused Playwright tests:
  - Client updates after event without reload.
  - Reload obtains the same state by fetch.
  - Event followed by reload does not regress display.

